< Text>
My boyfriend and I knew we were going to be in the market for a new bed. We wanted to wait till presidents day to shop around hoping we would get some good deals. Our first stop was Mattress firm on Bascom and met with John Wise. He happily showed us around the floor helping us realize what kind of bed we wanted to begin with, considering we didn't really put to much thought or research in to it. He was extremely helpful and very patient with us. He understood that purchasing a bed was an investment and needed to be carefully thought out. My Mike ended up find one that he really liked, however we wanted to make sure we explored all our options. So we left and went to lunch, visited a few more mattress store locations, sat on some more beds, broke down our budget and decided that the original mattress at mattress firm was the one he liked the best. John was more than happy we were able to find the mattress that fit our needs. He was able to add some fun free goodies in the purchase to as the mattress we bought wasn't cheap. He was a joy to work with! He kept us laughing the whole time, made sure he was engaging with us constantly and kept it a rather relaxed environment. As a matter of fact, the whole team at this locations was pretty amazing and very attentive. Thank you for all your assistance and making this a wonderful fun experience.

Sincerely
Two happy bed buyers!< /Text>

<rate>5</rate>< Text>
Obtaining MBI coverage in California can be challenging. The most advertised company doesn't offer coverage in Ca. Options are limited and some have many hurdles like waiting periods of 30 days and 1000 miles(both have to be met) Note: Driving 1000 miles during Lockdown Pandemic orders is nearly impossible anytime soon. Most don't offer a payment plan option either, so pony up $$$ or nothing. However this is not the case with Olive at all. No waiting periods of any kind, payment plans (no fee) choose from 3 different deductibles, provide basic info on car and a payment source and you're done!

<user>107882015149670976723< /user>< Name>
Merlin Silk</Name>
<date>1462319363454</date><Rate>2< /Rate>< review>
I needed some friends to get a document notarized. To make it easy for them I looked for a mobile notary and found Seals on Wheels just two blocks from my friends house. The pricing on their web site said $10 per signature and $20 and up for mobile/convenience fee. At less than two miles from my friends house I though hmm, $40 for the two signatures including the mobile fee - good! I called Leslie and she could make it. Was not a rush - about 3 hours after I called. The phone connection was so bad that I could not really talk about details, but it all worked out. My friends told me that Leslie was very nice and it got done. I had arranged with Leslie that I would pay for the service and things were not that nice any more when she texted me the amount she wanted from me: $70!
Obviously I wondered why $50 more for a trip of 1.9 miles (per google maps)? She backed down to $60 immediately, but I was not sure that I had remembered the price correctly, but yes, I had.
When I did not immediately pay (to take another look at the website) she threatened me to go back to my friends and collect the documents, strong-arming me into paying immediately. I also got a call from an Alex who claimed to be running this business and I could not stop him talking trying to justify the price. Like, that is not really our address, we don't have an office, only mobile sewrvice and then the most ridiculous, that the mobile fee depended on where Leslie came from. So, I guess when he manages to schedule clients as far a part as possible he will make a killing in mobile fees.
I gave them the option to rethink their position and refund some of my money, but I think they needed the money more than my good will and my good review. Two stars because the service was good and friendly, but loss of three stars for me feeling ripped off. For $40 I would have asked my friends to go to the next notary - there are plenty in Van Nuys.</review>

< text>
Had not been inside Costco since February and was pleasantly surprised about the balance between safety and normalcy.  I found the self check-out to be a huge improvement for those of us that have just a few items.  Most customers seemed to be social distancing and all were masked.  Costco continues to provide an effective business model during uncertain times.  I have also found the gas stations at Costco to be a safe haven from rising costs in so many other areas of life.  Another great deal noted below.  Keep up the good work!</text>

Super busy location. I would recommend arriving at the time the store opens to mitigate the effects of large crowd sizes. < Review>
My car had a flat tire, and I took it out and verified the leak location where was in repairable area.  While I did a leaking test in the whole tire, it was only one leaking spot.   I called Costco tire department , and they told me that fixing flat tire is $10.99.  I would like to have patch fix inside the tire instead of using plug stick from outside, so I took it to there.  Guess what, the price change to $15.99 because they insisted to charge $5 for rebalance the tire, and the repair fee was not refundable if the tire was not repairable condition.  At that time, I was not happy about it because I felt like being robbed.
They have many cars for tire service and they are busy too, they don't care much whether to have my business or not.  Since I already drove all the way to Costco, I didn't want to wast more time to visit other place, so I paid they to do my flat tire repair.  3 hours later, they called me that they found two leaking holes on my tire and not repairable because to leaking spots less than 18 inches apart, and I needed to buy a new tire.   When I get there, they showed me that the tire they had in store for the replacement was about $200.  I doubted about their test result, so I decided to take my tire back.  I asked if they can refund the "tire rebalance" fee since they didn't do that service, and they said "NO".
After I have my tire back home, I test the leaking again.  The second spot that Costco tire technician indicated as leaking was not true, it does has any leaks.  Finally, I use a glue stick flat tire repair kit to fix my tire  that less than 5 min work.

Long story short, Fremont Costco Tire Service is really sucks. If your car's tires not purchased from them in the being, recommend don't go there for  the service.<//Review>

< Rating>
3</Rating>
< Text>
I love Costco and it's my go to store for all shopping needs. This store is located off Auto Mall parkway in a very densely populated shopping plaza and has gas station. We just popped in there to see what the liquor prices looked like since we live in Oregon and down for my son's graduation. Costco in Oregon does not sell liquor and the taxes at the Costco in WA make the prices crazy. I always tell people the only thing in Cali that is cheap is liquor...go figure since you need a stiff drink to deall with the 1,000,000 other people who decide to go to the same place as you at the same time...maybe Thanos was on to something. Anyway, when you enter the parking lot, avoid going pas the intersection in front of the store entry...a mix of peope in cars and walking and not paying attention so just park far away and do something amazing like walk. Don't follow the lady that just came out the store with her full cart all the way through the parking lot like you about to do a drive by...there is plenty of parking. The biggest issue I had with this place...hence the 3 stars. The food court. So, they have the remote pay terminals so you can order your food and pay for it. Well the thing spits out a receipt with a number on it so I figured they would call my number. Nope, after that, we had to get into a line behind 20 other people to get to the counter to hand your receipt to someone just so they can make your order...who is the idiiot that thought this was smart? Meanwhile, the line to pay cash had no one waiting and the person there would only help if you paid cash. I was this close from letting the manager know how dumb this was but...it's not my Costco. Back to Oregon I go with lots of liquor on your cheap taxes. Good bye Cali. Remember...don't move to Oregon...stay here.</Text>

<review>(Translated by Google) This wholesaler has a special place in the hearts of its customers. First, because they are special. Different from stores that have a membership system, usually non-members can enter, but only members who get a special price. However, Vostco is different. Only members can enter the store, while getting a discounted price. This shows that Costco is very concerned about membership in his shop. In fact, the ones who get the discount are not only the ones in the store but also the fuel!

That day, I was escorted by a Costco member shopping there. I need a lot of souvenirs for friends. Thankfully, there was an appropriate discount on the items I needed.

The goods sold are various. Not just daily needs, but also collectible items and books.

When paying, after the discount price, there is still a $ 3.50 discount, so the price is cheap.

With treatment that prioritizes customer satisfaction, a large parking yard, of course, this shop is loved by its customers.

(Original)
